Requirements:
Neovim >= 0.8.0
Git >= 2.19.0
nodejs >= 14.14
GCC and G++

Set up:
0.1.- Install Neovim (download appimage file and insert it into a PATH directory, like /usr/local/bin)
0.2.- Install nodejs the same way (create directory for all the files, add /usr/local/node/bin to PATH)

1. Clone the repository in the ~/.config directory and rename it to "nvim"
2. Open nvim on terminal and let it install all plugins
3. Go into ~/.local/share/nvim/lazy/coc.nvim and run the following commands:
    sudo npm install -g yarn
    yarn install
    yarn build
4. Install LSP's
    Open any .c file
    :CocCommand clangd.install
